Defendant Jose M Gonzalez in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Shawna Stevenoski sworn as Spanish Interpreter.

off-record: 9:02 - 9:06 am 
On Motion of the State, the Court AMENDS Count #1 to Disorderly Conduct contrary to 947.01(1), a Class B misdemeanor

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on AMENDED charge; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
ADA Hall submits victim impact statement

Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:
--No presence at the residence of Josephine Bartlett or any location temporarily occupied by her
--To undergo any type of assessment, treatment or counseling as required by his Agent
--No direct or indirect contact with Josephine Bartlett
--No possession of any dangerous weapons

Case called at 10:09am [mo]
[Competency Hearing]
Defendant Jose M Gonzalez in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa.   ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Shock verifies victim rights compliance

Shawna Stevenoski--sworn as Spanish Interpreter

Interpreter Stevenoski discloses that she was the interpreter for the Competency Examination with the doctor

Atty. De La Rosa and ADA Shock verifies receipt of the Examiner's Report 
Mr. Gonzalez claims to be competent; waives his right to present evidence beyond that in the examiners report
Atty. De La Rosa waives the right to present evidence. 
ADA Shock informs the Court that the State believes Mr. Gonzalez is competent; waives right to present evidence. 

The Court finds that the examiners report indicates that Mr. Gonzalez IS competent
The Court finds Mr. Gonzalez to be competent.
The Court and Counsel discuss scheduling.
The Court directs the State to determine the availability of witnesses for the Preliminary Hearing by 11/16/15 at 4:00pm, if the State determines there is a witness unavailable then the State is to correspond with Atty. De La Rosa and the Court JA to schedule a new Preliminary Hearing, on 11/16/15 by 4:00pm also. 
recess: 10:18am
